verbs.description: outrock (third-person singular simple present outrocks, present participle outrocking, simple past and past participle outrocked)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To surpass in rocking (thrilling or exciting, especially with rock music).
examples: Love vows to outrock the cooler-than-thou swish kids — and succeeds — chanting "Gabba-gabba baby" and "Shut up!" until there's a puddle of sweat on the floorboards.
